article.headline: Loyola (Md.) 80, Siena 57
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. -- Dylon Cormier scored 24 points and Robert Olson added 20 as Loyola (Md.) won its second straight and fourth in five in beating Siena 80-57 Saturday night. Cormier was 6-of-12 shooting and knocked down 3 of 7 from deep and 9 of 10 at the foul line for the Greyhounds (19-9, 11-5 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Olson was 6-of-10 shooting and 4 of 6 from 3-point range. The game was the 120th of Olson's career, moving him ahead of Marquis Sullivan for third on the program's all-time games played list. He's four shy of Brian Rudolph for the program record. Erik Etherly added 11 points and Julius Brooks 10 for Loyola, which shot 52.8 percent (28 of 53) and made 8 of 15 3-pointers. Trenity Burdine scored 12 points and O.D. Anosike had 10 with seven rebounds for the Saints (6-21, 4-12), who have lost five straight.
